<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,329,930]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,725,750]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
Three-colour morphotypes were found: yellowish with a delicate reticulated pattern on the dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[159,255,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1879,1901]" captionTargetBox="[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, Berthella martensi (MB28-004607). B–D, Berthellina delicata species complex (MB28-005057, MB28- 004578, MB28-005060, respectively). E, Berthellina sp. (MB28-005016). F, Pleurobranchaea brockii (in situ). G, Pleurobranchus albiguttatus (MB28-004603). H–I, Pleurobranchus forskalii (MB28-004434 and MHN-YT1655, respectively). J, Pleurobranchus grandis (in situ). K–L, Pleurobranchus peronii (MHN-YT276 and MB28-005042, respectively)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069172/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
); a translucent yellow body with low yellow tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[885,982,761,786]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1879,1901]" captionTargetBox="[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, Berthella martensi (MB28-004607). B–D, Berthellina delicata species complex (MB28-005057, MB28- 004578, MB28-005060, respectively). E, Berthellina sp. (MB28-005016). F, Pleurobranchaea brockii (in situ). G, Pleurobranchus albiguttatus (MB28-004603). H–I, Pleurobranchus forskalii (MB28-004434 and MHN-YT1655, respectively). J, Pleurobranchus grandis (in situ). K–L, Pleurobranchus peronii (MHN-YT276 and MB28-005042, respectively)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069172/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2 C</figureCitation>
); and an orange body with white specks (
<figureCitation box="[159,260,797,822]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1879,1901]" captionTargetBox="[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[218,1354,195,1865]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, Berthella martensi (MB28-004607). B–D, Berthellina delicata species complex (MB28-005057, MB28- 004578, MB28-005060, respectively). E, Berthellina sp. (MB28-005016). F, Pleurobranchaea brockii (in situ). G, Pleurobranchus albiguttatus (MB28-004603). H–I, Pleurobranchus forskalii (MB28-004434 and MHN-YT1655, respectively). J, Pleurobranchus grandis (in situ). K–L, Pleurobranchus peronii (MHN-YT276 and MB28-005042, respectively)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1069172/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2 D</figureCitation>
). The variety of habitats, depths and specimen colours suggest that the animals collected here probably represent a complex of species. The systematics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gardiner" authorityYear="1936" box="[804,930,833,858]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pleurobranchidae" genus="Berthellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurobranchomorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,930,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Berthellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Indo-Pacific are in need of a comprehensive review (
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera" box="[427,660,869,894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Cervera, J. L., Gosliner, T. M. &amp; Garcia-Gomes, J. C. (1999) The systematics of Berthellina: many varieties of oranges. In: Abstracts of the Systematics, Phylogeny and Biology of Opisthobranch Molluscs. 2 nd International Workshop of Malacology, Menfi, June 10 - 14, 1999. Istituzione Culturale Federico II °, Menfi, pp. unumbered." type="journal article" year="1999">
Cervera 
<emphasis box="[529,590,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moustafa" box="[676,925,869,894]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Moustafa, A. Y., Golestani, H. &amp; Valdes, A. (2016) A review of the genus Berthellina (Mollusca: Heterobranchia: Pleurobranchidae) in the Red Sea based on molecular and anatomical data. Marine Biodiversity, August 2016, 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 016 - 0558 - 2" type="journal article" year="2016">
Moustafa 
<emphasis box="[793,854,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
), because this taxon is indistinguishable by external characteristics alone (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardiner" box="[490,658,905,930]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Gardiner, A. P. (1936) Engel's paper on &quot; The English species of the family Pleurobranchidae. &quot; Journal of Conchology, 20, 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1936">Gardiner 1936</bibRefCitation>
; Gosliner 
<emphasis box="[773,829,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2008; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvim" box="[907,1174,905,930]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Alvim, J. &amp; Pimenta, A. D. (2015) Taxonomic review of Berthella and Berthellina (Gastropoda: Pleurobranchoidea) from Brazil, with description of two new species. Zoologia, 32, 497 - 531. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 1984 - 46702015000600010" type="journal article" year="2015">Alvim &amp; Pimenta 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
